			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Broker Fahaan</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=535088"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:evilhinkle@hotmail.com">Josh Hinkle</a> | 
		                        12/19/2001 11:47:24 AM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">There are many trade skills quests to be done by giving your slate to varios merchants that are asking for people who need work when you hail them.  This one is for your tailoring skill, only im stuck on it.  Give your slate to Broker Fahaan and he gives you a bag to pput four young hopper hides in, combine bag and give back to him, he gives you a stretched hopper hide and a leather strap. do this four times and then turn in the four leather straps. He then gives you a knife and tells you to combine that with a MQ hopper hide to get a rough belt strap. I dont remeber if he asks for the knofe back or not but i gave it to him and had to get all the hides again ( so if he needs the nife back be sure to cut a few extra belt straps. When you turn in the strap (and knife?) he gives you a vah shir needle kit and tells you to make a black chittin belt and a bone beaded belt. This is where i am stuck, he says you need to combine the needle kit, xakra silk, a scorpion carapace, and a belt strap to make the black chittin belt but either i have the wrong components or its bugged. If anyone completes the belt please post the correct components and where they are found.
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
