	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Just a little clarification. The belts are NODROP and LORE, so you can't hand them to another player to hold. The needle set is LORE as well, but it isn't NODROP, so the only way you can keep a belt for yourself is to make an extra rough belt strap to take along to turn in to the Broker. When you get both belts made, take along a friend to hold your needle set for you. Give your friend your needle set and hand the Broker the extra rough belt strap for a second needle set. Turn this needle set in with your two belts for the next quest. You can then retrieve your original needle set from your friend to make yourself another Black Chitin belt, or the Bone Beaded belt if you'd prefer. Both are pretty nice belts for non-twinked newbies. I'd highly recommend you keep the needle set to continue tailoring belts with, especially if you haven't trivialed with them yet. Carapaces, silk, and Medium Quality hopper hides are fairly easy to come by, and this is an inexpensive way to continue raising your tailoring skill.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
